\f0\b \cf0 Constructing a geometrical quasi-MOM\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural

\f1\b0 \cf0 \
Consider first the situation without any quasi-relator.  In this case, the O(1) cusp graph is a tree -- the unique path to any group element can be read off from its representation as a word.\
\
Adding a quasi-relator adds extra connections in the graph, creating closed circuits which start and end at the infinity horoball.  By following one of these circuits, adding the implied triangle for each edge traversed, we have a complex of triangles.  In practice, by following the most obvious circuits, we find that the structure is in fact a geometrical quasi-MOM.\
